<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="362" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1581,1966]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,374,1581,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Length (incl. forewing) 
<quantity box="[664,749,1582,1606]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
; head width (incl. eyes) 
<quantity box="[1039,1132,1582,1606]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width 
<quantity box="[1340,1432,1582,1606]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="362" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Body generally rufous, more yellowish ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[740,810,1617,1642]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,210,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1400,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Elongationa hyalina sp. nov. 1 habitus, dorsal view; 2, habitus, lateral view; 3, forewing; 4, face; 5, anal tube and appendages, lateral view; 6, pygofer side, lateral view; 7, male 8 th sternite, ventral view; 8, magnified aedeagus, ventral view; 9, aedeagus, style and connective, later view; 10, subgenital plate, ventral view; 11, connective, dorsal view; 12, magnified process of pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 1 - 7, 9 - 12); 0.4 mm (Figs. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Crown and apical half of face, dark brown, lateral margins of crown basally and pronotum edged yellowish white (
<figureCitation box="[875,941,1653,1678]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,210,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1400,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Elongationa hyalina sp. nov. 1 habitus, dorsal view; 2, habitus, lateral view; 3, forewing; 4, face; 5, anal tube and appendages, lateral view; 6, pygofer side, lateral view; 7, male 8 th sternite, ventral view; 8, magnified aedeagus, ventral view; 9, aedeagus, style and connective, later view; 10, subgenital plate, ventral view; 11, connective, dorsal view; 12, magnified process of pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 1 - 7, 9 - 12); 0.4 mm (Figs. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Fore wing with basal costal margin edged with dark brown basally; elongate hyaline band medially from base to apex of wing (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1172,1689,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,210,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1400,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Elongationa hyalina sp. nov. 1 habitus, dorsal view; 2, habitus, lateral view; 3, forewing; 4, face; 5, anal tube and appendages, lateral view; 6, pygofer side, lateral view; 7, male 8 th sternite, ventral view; 8, magnified aedeagus, ventral view; 9, aedeagus, style and connective, later view; 10, subgenital plate, ventral view; 11, connective, dorsal view; 12, magnified process of pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 1 - 7, 9 - 12); 0.4 mm (Figs. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Pronotum slightly depressed laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1581,1966]" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">
Male pygofer with dorsal edge sinuate and long finger-like process apically (
<figureCitation box="[1099,1171,1761,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,210,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1400,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Elongationa hyalina sp. nov. 1 habitus, dorsal view; 2, habitus, lateral view; 3, forewing; 4, face; 5, anal tube and appendages, lateral view; 6, pygofer side, lateral view; 7, male 8 th sternite, ventral view; 8, magnified aedeagus, ventral view; 9, aedeagus, style and connective, later view; 10, subgenital plate, ventral view; 11, connective, dorsal view; 12, magnified process of pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 1 - 7, 9 - 12); 0.4 mm (Figs. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Style apex triangular laterally (
<figureCitation box="[257,325,1797,1822]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,210,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1400,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Elongationa hyalina sp. nov. 1 habitus, dorsal view; 2, habitus, lateral view; 3, forewing; 4, face; 5, anal tube and appendages, lateral view; 6, pygofer side, lateral view; 7, male 8 th sternite, ventral view; 8, magnified aedeagus, ventral view; 9, aedeagus, style and connective, later view; 10, subgenital plate, ventral view; 11, connective, dorsal view; 12, magnified process of pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 1 - 7, 9 - 12); 0.4 mm (Figs. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus flat, curved dorsally and tapering apically, with pair of long spinelike processes basally, second pair of lamelliform footlike processes medially (
<figureCitation box="[777,885,1833,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,210,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1400,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Elongationa hyalina sp. nov. 1 habitus, dorsal view; 2, habitus, lateral view; 3, forewing; 4, face; 5, anal tube and appendages, lateral view; 6, pygofer side, lateral view; 7, male 8 th sternite, ventral view; 8, magnified aedeagus, ventral view; 9, aedeagus, style and connective, later view; 10, subgenital plate, ventral view; 11, connective, dorsal view; 12, magnified process of pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 1 - 7, 9 - 12); 0.4 mm (Figs. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Figs. 8, 9</figureCitation>
); gonopore apical on dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[1300,1396,1833,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[236,1350,210,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1400,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Elongationa hyalina sp. nov. 1 habitus, dorsal view; 2, habitus, lateral view; 3, forewing; 4, face; 5, anal tube and appendages, lateral view; 6, pygofer side, lateral view; 7, male 8 th sternite, ventral view; 8, magnified aedeagus, ventral view; 9, aedeagus, style and connective, later view; 10, subgenital plate, ventral view; 11, connective, dorsal view; 12, magnified process of pygofer, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 1 - 7, 9 - 12); 0.4 mm (Figs. 8)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="362">Fig. 8, 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
